def: A division of Protozoa in which a mouthlike opening exists.
An extensive division of Anthozoa, including most of thespecies that produce stony corals. See Illust. of Anthozoa.-- Mad`re*po*ra"ri*an, a. & n.
A genus of plants, the type of which is mignonette.
Pertaining to, or exhibiting, poles; having a polar arrangementor disposition; arising from, or dependent upon, the possession ofpoles or polar characteristics; as, polaristic antagonism.
The practices of a mountebank; mountebankery.
The number of guns carried by a ship of war.
Tin ore scarcely perceptible in the stone; tin ore stamped veryfine. Pryce.
An order of ganoid fishes, including the sturgeons; -- socalled on account of their cartilaginous skeleton.
A cry, as of a chicken,; a whining or whimpering.Leave this faint puling and lament as I do. Shak.
